<TITLE> Govt hikes BRTC bus fares </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 7 (bdnews24.com)  The government has reset the fares of diesel-run buses operated by Bangladesh Road Transport Corporation due to the fuel's price hike, a government statement said Sunday. The new fares set Tk 1.20 per km for double-decker buses in Dhaka city and Tk 1.05 per km for inter-district and long-distant buses. The fare list is effective from Sunday. bdnews
